Of the dark influence on the flight of space probes
For years, a mysterious phenomenon leaves researchers in the concern: The dark influence on the speed of space probes during the games gravitationnel support.
Experts fear that the general theory of relativity is not entirely correct.
For nearly 18 years, the space borehole "Ulysses" steals in the area.
Of fuel conductions soon be frozen, death cryogène the threat.
For years, a mysterious phenomenon is because of confusion among researchers - the anomaly of the support gravitationnel.
The support gravitationnel is a manoeuvre of space probes, for which they get an extra boost in the field gravitationnel a heavenly bodies, the Earth for example.
Thus, the probes can save a lot of fuel.
The research borehole américo-European Casini-Huygens used this device physical, just as the solar borehole Ulysses.
That is what surprised the researchers also for years: Objects kites are not always 100 percent of the way in which it expects to the venerable institution laws of gravity.
Much more irregularities occur in the speed.
The probes become so unexpected faster or slower.
Until now, physicists could not explain this.
They as the anomaly of the support gravitationnel.
Some experts fear that the theory of general relativity Albert Einstein, which describes the power of attraction of the area because of the curvature of the area, may not be entirely correct.
The American physicist Stephen Adler of the Institute for Advanced Study in Princeton still believes unshaken that Einstein do not was wrong and is trying to explain the anomaly of the support gravitationnel with the help of the so-called black matters that astronomers have identified in the universe.
"This black might be responsible for this anomaly, who is also in the vicinity of the Earth," he writes.
Researchers of space know about the only black for about ten years.
It is apparently it a force of attraction whose effect is visible on other bodies.
It is entirely invisible, i.e. that it sends nor does not reflect electromagnetic radiation, especially no visible light.
According to the calculations of scientists, the black matters would be a good fifth of the mass of the universe.
