Despite everything, nothing has changed.
If tourists in Manhattan was far from the newsstand and giant TV screens of Times Square, they do not make that they are in the eye of the storm.
Never they might think that in the offices in glass and nest of bee above their tète, bankers and hedge fund managers who monopolize New York, are the worst "working day at the office" since the fall of 1929.
The men continue to squeeze on the pavements, with their trolleys and their shelves of muffins for meetings matinières.
