"I photograph the master outside the scene to capture of the elements of his character" Günther Bauer - photographer
Or heels of transgressing or clothes.
The essence of the great masters of the intoxicating spirit of flamenco, released all tensions to get the relaxed aspect of the man or woman.
On the one hand the artist.
On the other, the person.
Inseparable except in the unknown intimacy, in these times of the public, where we discover to intimate and gestures of sight stolen of artists who do not care about up on stage.
German Günther Bauer mixture in "intoxicating spirit of flamenco - people 'the théâtralité of a few stage with singers, dancers and guitaristes with this side least-known artists.
In this project, the photographer takes up the special iconography of the intoxicating spirit of flamenco from different angles.
Included in the programming of the Month of the photograph Flanders, the exhibition "reflects the international importance of the intoxicating spirit of flamenco, more every day," explains the creator, which clarifies that "intoxicating spirit of flamenco - people '" can be anyone but, having seen the pictures, the observer realise that they are not typical images of artists on stage.
These people photographiées "in the street artists' are able to pass on stage of the passion, the sadness, the joy... in exciting the public.
To capture the moment of personality of these artists we should not make photos on stage.
They have a personality and a unique character.
I am interested it was to create an intimate atmosphere to be able to capture with the camera of moments of personality of the stars of the intoxicating spirit of flamenco ".
With the popular song festival "of Mines," Bauer began in 1997 a long journey to photographed the singers, dancers guitaristes or with a camera to mark.
Portraits of which, thanks to the choice of the camera and equipment, given the photograph classic.
The implementation of various means stylistic breaks with the classic side of the image, with a touch of modernity, this reflects the perception of the intoxicating spirit of flamenco in Bauer: "A very traditional music with roots that is changing and surprises us every day."
It is not the dancing and singing itself, but of personality and the nature of the artist who ogre the public with his art.
The search for the essential and the magic has been the constant of this work that is presented these days to the gallery El Fotómata.
The stars of the intoxicating spirit of flamenco as Diego El Cigala, Chano Lobato, Cristina Hoyos, Enrique Morente, El Lebrijano, Antonio Canales, Vicente Amigo, among others, are part of the selection made from around seventy artists photographed.
The project has turned into a anthologie the intoxicating spirit of flamenco, which will soon be published in a book of collecting portraits exposed to the gallery.
Passion for the portraits of Bauer has led to repeat the idea two years ago with the "portraits of old athletes' ('SportARTproject").
Although the concepts are different in "intoxicating spirit of flamenco - people ', the photographer admits that he loves photographed the portrait of people know them, and to enter their lives for a moment more or less long.
I believe that in the photograph the portrait is the kind of the most difficult.
You trouves in front of people, of characters that sometimes you do not know or are you just a few minutes to make them a photograph.
Despite these circumstances, as photographer, I always try that my ideas reality ".
