The stock market values of Warsaw has proposed two hundred million, about five billion kronor Czech, for the purchase of 100% of the package of actions of the stock market values of Prague.
Ludwik Sobolewski, the chairman of the stock market values of Warsaw, confirmed this proposal that the Polish have made despite that, before, the Czechs have ruled out the stock exchange of Warsaw the circle of potential new owners of the stock market in Prague.
The cause of this exclusion is that the stock exchange of Warsaw is owned by the state.
99% of the shares are in the hands of the Polish state who wants to secede from more than 60% of its actions in a few months of activities.
According to the Czech business daily E15, the Polish proposal represents the most high that has been made to date for the purchase of the stock market in Prague.
Czech according to the press, the stock exchange of Vienna, the transatlantic exchange, the Nasdaq Stock Exchange of New York, the stock exchange in London and Deutsche Börse have made an offer to date.
